与贝克的浪漫关系</a>。贝克最近还<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-julien-baker-and-jasmine-4-t-cover-system-of-a-down-at-sxsw-2025-3846752">用茉莉花（Jasmine）进行了Down的“毒性”经典系统的封面。4.T在SXSW 2025上</a>。</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/julien-baker-torres-share-new-single-dirt-and-cancel-shows-due-to-concussion-3849534">朱利安·贝克（Julien Baker）和托雷斯（Torres）的邮政分享了新的单曲“污垢”，并且由于脑震荡而导致的取消节目</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
凯文·康明斯（Kevin Cummins https://www.nme.com/news/music/kevin-cummins-announces-new-oasis-book-book-the-masterplan-featuran-featuran-loads-unpelly-photos-photos-3849525?u tm_source = rss＆utm_medium = rss＆utm_campaign = kevin-cummins-new-oasis-oasis-book-book-the-masterplan-featerplan-featerplan-loads-unperply-PhotosPoppy Burton Wed, 26 Mar 2025 20:29:23 +0000 Music NewsNewsIndie https://www.nme.com/?p=3849525 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-featured.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="绿洲" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-featured.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-featured-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-featured-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-featured-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-featured-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-featured-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>这本书还带来了诺埃尔·加拉格尔（Noel Gallagher）的贡献，他对足球，时尚和对绿洲成长时代的记忆分享了自己的想法</p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/kevin-cummins-announces-new-oasis-book-the-masterplan-featuring-loads-of-unpublished-photos-3849525">凯文·康明斯（Kevin Cummins）的帖子宣布了新的绿洲书《总体规划》（The Masterplan），其中包含大量未出版的照片，</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-featured.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="绿洲" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-featured.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-featured-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-featured-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-featured-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-featured-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-featured-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>著名的音乐摄影师凯文·康明斯（Kevin Cummins）宣布了一本新书<em><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/oasis">《 Oasis</a> ：</em> <em>The Masterplan》</em> ，其中包含许多先前未出版的Gallagher Brothers镜头。</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/oasis-2025-reunion-dream-setlist-3788142">Supersonic setlist：绿洲需要在2025年聚会之旅中玩什么</a></strong></li></ul><p>在乐队职业生涯的开始之初，这本新书使歌迷从未见过“十二个月的地震变化，巩固了绿洲的身份”，从未见过兄弟。</p><p>正如<a href="https://www.nme.com/photos/classic-nme-photography-by-kevin-cummins-1428785">前<em>NME</em>摄影师</a>最近<a href="https://www.threads.net/@kcmanc" target="_blank" rel="noopener">详细</a>介绍了从<a href="https://www.nme.com/photos/joy-division-by-kevin-cummins-1418947">伊恩·柯蒂斯（Ian Curtis）</a>到<a href="/artists/David-Bowie">大卫·鲍伊（David Bowie）</a>的所有人，他在九十年代初被带到了他们的突破中：“我被委托用各种照明，位置和风格的各种照明，以了解最适合他们的创造记录。 </p><figure id="attachment_3849545" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3849545" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3849545" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-2.jpg" alt="绿洲" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-2.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-2-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-2-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-2-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-2-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-2-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3849545" class="wp-caption-text">英国摇滚乐队Oasis的Noel和Liam Gallagher在曼彻斯特峰酒吧外面，1994年8月2日。</figcaption></figure><p>这本书绘制了“刚刚购买的宫殿宫殿的可实现宫殿的可实现”，这本书有望展示乐队如何开发出来的标志性声音和风格，以代表英国独立舞台。</p><p>明天（3月27日），您可以<a href="https://linktr.ee/oasismasterplan" target="_blank" rel="noopener">在此处</a>查看库存商和独家。这也带来了诺埃尔·加拉格尔（Noel Gallagher）的贡献，他分享了他对足球，时尚和对成长时代的记忆的想法。同样，它带有康明斯本人的话，以及盖尔·克劳瑟（Gail Crowther）的文化评论。</p><p>展望<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-reunion-tour-uk-ireland-stadium-2025-liam-noel-gallagher-tickets-3787539">今年夏天的地标聚会展览</a>，那些接近这次巡回演出的人<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-line-up-band-reunion-tour-members-2025-3845348">揭示了</a>谁将在<em>NME乐队</em>阵容中演奏的人。他们说，安迪·贝尔（Andy Bell）将在吉他上乘坐低音，宝石Archer和Paul“ Bonehead” Arthurs，而Joey Waronker则将在鼓上。 </p><figure id="attachment_3849544" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3849544" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3849544" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-3.jpg" alt="绿洲" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-3.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-3-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-3-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-3-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-3-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-3-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3849544" class="wp-caption-text"> Oasis（Noel Gallagher，Liam Gallagher，Paul McGuigan，Paul Arthurs，Tony McCarroll）在伦敦Soho，1994年3月15日。</figcaption></figure><p><em>绿洲的“ Live&#39;25</em>团圆巡回赛”将于7月4日星期五在加的夫开始，这将是今年<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-reunion-tour-uk-ireland-stadium-2025-liam-noel-gallagher-tickets-3787539">在欧洲唯一在欧洲演出的长期演出</a>，然后乐队前往<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-announce-2025-reunion-tour-dates-in-north-america-and-mexico-buy-tickets-3798246">北美</a>， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-announce-2025-south-american-reunion-tour-dates-the-brothers-are-coming-buy-tickets-3809661">南美</a>， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-announce-australian-dates-of-live-25-reunion-tour-buy-tickets-3800091">澳大利亚</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-announce-south-korean-and-japan-dates-for-their-2025-reunion-tour-3814881">亚洲的</a>体育场。</p><p>自八月份宣布以来，虔诚的绿洲球迷一直在等待绿洲聚会。 29岁的Oasis爱好者和曼彻斯特的体育作家Razz Ashraf <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/music-features/oasis-reunion-manchester-sifters-mural-3790147">在一项有关乐队回到家乡的演讲中与<em>NME</em>发表讲话</a>，向记者加里·瑞安（Gary Ryan）开放，同时在Sifters Records  -  Gallagher Brothers曾经在1994年的Shakermaker&#39;and Inshore中访问并在这里进行的纪录和姓名来访问，并在这里进行了启动： </p><figure id="attachment_3849543" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3849543" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3849543" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-1.jpg" alt="绿洲" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/live-oasis-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3849543" class="wp-caption-text"> 1994年5月8日，伦敦东部Sly St Studio的英国摇滚乐队Oasis的Noel Gallagher。信贷：出版社</figcaption></figure><p>他补充说：“我对此感到非常激动。我一直在幻想这一刻。”他的父亲会在房子周围玩绿洲。 “他对岩石的兴趣不大，但是由于他们来自曼彻斯特，他能理解。当我开始与我的城市建立更多的联系时，他们开始对我来说意义重大。”</p><p>同时， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-announce-live-25-reunion-tour-film-produced-by-peaky-blinders-creator-steven-knight-3846000">乐队还宣布了一部名为<em>“ Live &#39;25 Live &#39;25”</em>的电影，将与巡回演出一起制作</a><em>，</em>该电影将由<em>Peaky Blinders</em>创作者<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/steven-knight">史蒂文·奈特（Steven Knight）</a>制作，并从Dylan Southern和Will Lovelace（以<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/LCD-Soundsystem">LCD Soundsystem</a>纪录片的<em>关闭并打了命中率而闻名）。</em></p><p>乐队最近<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-announce-25th-anniversary-standing-on-the-shoulder-of-giants-reissue-3835860">重新发行了他们的第四张专辑《 Stand on the Giants》，以纪念其成立25周年</a>，并与<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kendrick-lamar">肯德里克·拉马尔（Kendrick Lamar）</a>进行了简短的排行榜大战，因为<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-on-course-to-hit-number-one-with-whatever-after-31-years-3840551">乙烯基重新释放了经典单曲“ Whather Whtwath Whathing”，威胁要在31年后获得第一名</a>。</p><p>绿洲被<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/oasis-new-order-the-white-stripes-mariah-carey-lead-nominations-for-rock-and-roll-hall-of-fame-2025-3837368">提名为今年的摇滚名人堂</a>，以及新秩序，白色条纹和玛丽亚·凯里（Mariah Carey）之类的人，但<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/liam-gallagher-says-rock-and-roll-hall-of-fame-is-for-wankers-after-oasis-nominated-3837513">利亚姆（Liam）继续坚持认为，这一荣誉是“为wankers</a> ”。</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/kevin-cummins-announces-new-oasis-book-the-masterplan-featuring-loads-of-unpublished-photos-3849525">凯文·康明斯（Kevin Cummins）的帖子宣布了新的绿洲书《总体规划》（The Masterplan），其中包含大量未出版的照片，</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
联合主任声称，奥斯卡拒绝发表声明以支持被绑架的巴勒斯坦电影制片人。 https://www.nme.com/news/film/soscars-refused-to-sissue-statement-in-support-of-kid-kidnapp--palstinian-filmmaker-filmmaker-co-director-colaims-3849496？ut m_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=oscars-refused-to-issue-statement-in-support-of-kidnapped-palestinian-filmmaker-co-director-claimsChris Edwards Wed, 26 Mar 2025 19:52:23 +0000 Film NewsNewsOscars https://www.nme.com/?p=3849496 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/hamdan-ballal.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Hamdan Ballal at the 74th Berlinale. CREDIT: Monika Skolimowska via Getty Images" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/hamdan-ballal.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/hamdan-ballal-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/hamdan-ballal-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/hamdan-ballal-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/hamdan-ballal-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/hamdan-ballal-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> &quot;The Academy was silent when the filmmaker they honoured needed them most&quot;</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/oscars-refused-to-issue-statement-in-support-of-kidnapped-palestinian-filmmaker-co-director-claims-3849496">Oscars refused to issue statement in support of kidnapped Palestinian filmmaker, co-director claims</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/hamdan-ballal.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Hamdan Ballal at the 74th Berlinale. CREDIT: Monika Skolimowska via Getty Images" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/hamdan-ballal.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/hamdan-ballal-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/hamdan-ballal-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/hamdan-ballal-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/hamdan-ballal-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/hamdan-ballal-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> The Academy refused to issue a statement in support of kidnapped Palestinian filmmaker Hamdan Ballal, claims Yuval Abraham, one of the co-directors of the <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/oscars">Oscar</a> -winning documentary <em>No Other Land</em> .</p><p> Ballal was released by Israeli authorities on Tuesday (March 25) after Abraham wrote on X the day before that his co-director had <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/oscar-winning-palestinian-filmmaker-hamdan-ballal-attacked-israeli-settlers-freed-3848959">gone missing after being attacked</a> .</p><p> “A group of settlers just lynched Hamdan Ballal, co-director of our film <em>No Other Land</em> ,” Abraham wrote. “They beat him and he has injuries in his head and stomach, bleeding. Soldiers invaded the ambulance he called, and took him. No sign of him since.”</p><p> Reports of Ballal&#39;s attack and detainment sparked a petition calling for his release, as well as statements from organisations such as the International Documentary Association.</p><p> On Wednesday (March 26), Abraham criticised the Academy in a <a href="https://x.com/yuval_abraham/status/1904828586009252249" target="_blank" rel="noopener">post on X</a> for not issuing their own statement of support for Ballal.</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> Sadly, the US Academy, which awarded us an Oscar three weeks ago, declined to publicly support Hamdan Ballal while he was beaten and tortured by Israeli soldiers and settlers.</p><p> The European Academy voiced support, as did countless other award groups and festivals. Several US…</p><p> — Yuval Abraham יובל אברהם (@yuval_abraham) <a href="https://twitter.com/yuval_abraham/status/1904828586009252249?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">March 26, 2025</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p> “Sadly, the US Academy, which awarded us an Oscar three weeks ago, declined to publicly support Hamdan Ballal while he was beaten and tortured by Israeli soldiers and settlers,” he wrote.</p><p> “The European Academy voiced support, as did countless other award groups and festivals. Several US Academy members — especially in the documentary branch — pushed for a statement, but it was ultimately refused. We were told that because other Palestinians were beaten up in the settler attack, it could be considered unrelated to the film, so they felt no need to respond.”</p><p> Abraham continued: “In other words, while Hamdan was clearly targeted for making No Other Land (he recalled soldiers joking about the Oscar as they tortured him), he was also targeted for being Palestinian — like countless others every day who are disregarded. This, it seems, gave the Academy an excuse to remain silent when a filmmaker they honoured, living under Israeli occupation, needed them the most.</p><p> “It&#39;s not too late to change this stance. Even now, issuing a statement condemning the attack on Hamdan and the Masafer Yatta community would send a meaningful message and serve as a deterrent for the future.”</p><p> The Academy has not yet issued a response to Abraham&#39;s comments.</p><p> Speaking to <em>ABC News</em> from hospital, Ballal said he is “afraid”, adding: “I feel, when they attack me, I will lose my life.” He also told the outlet that he was severely beaten at the hands of Jewish settlers at his home on Monday, just outside the village of Susiya.</p><p> “It was a hard, hard attack,” Ballal said. “You know, I feel I will die, because this attack was so hard, I bleed from everywhere. I&#39;m crying from deeply in my heart. I feel pain everywhere in my body. So, they continue attacking me like 15-20 minutes,” he added, before also confirming the presence of  “soldiers with guns.”</p><p> Ballal directed <i>No Other Land</i> alongside Abraham, Basel Adra and Rachel Szor. The film chronicles the demolition of Palestinian homes in the West Bank between 2019 and 2023, and <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/best-documentary-oscar-winner-no-other-land-praised-for-moving-speech-on-palestine-3842824">won the Academy Award</a> for Best Documentary Feature at the <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/oscars-2025-winners-full-list-3842814#:~:text=Anora%20proved%20the%20big%20winner,Original%20Screenplay%20and%20Best%20Editing.">2025 ceremony</a> earlier this month. </p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3848962" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/no-other-land-oscars.jpg" alt="'No Other Land' directors Yuval Abraham, Rachel Szor, Hamdan Ballal and Basel Adra holding their Oscars for Best Documentary Feature. CREDIT: Arturo Holmes/WireImage via Getty Images" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/no-other-land-oscars.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/no-other-land-oscars-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/no-other-land-oscars-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/no-other-land-oscars-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/no-other-land-oscars-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/no-other-land-oscars-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> In a statement to <a href="https://news.sky.com/story/oscar-winning-palestinian-filmmaker-hamdan-ballal-detained-by-israeli-military-after-being-beaten-up-say-activists-13335246" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><i>Sky News</i></a> , the Israel Defence Forces (IDF) said that on the evening of March 24, “several terrorists hurled rocks at Israeli citizens, damaging their vehicles near Susya”, and a violent confrontation broke out which involved “mutual rock-hurling between Palestinians and Israelis at the scene”.</p><p> They continued: “IDF and Israeli Police forces arrived to disperse the confrontation, at this point, several terrorists began hurling rocks at the security forces.”</p><p> “In response, the forces apprehended three Palestinians suspected of hurling rocks at them, as well as an Israeli civilian involved in the violent confrontation. The detainees were taken for further questioning by the Israel police. An Israeli citizen was injured in the incident and was evacuated to receive medical treatment.</p><p> “Contrary to claims, no Palestinian was apprehended from inside an ambulance.”</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> Beaten savagely by illegal Israel “settlers” and when the ambulance arrived to help him he was abducted by the IDF.</p><p> This is Palestine every single day. A total and brutal occupation on every level imaginable.</p><p> FUCK US-BACKED ISRAEL <a href="https://t.co/KAn0VUMSlZ">pic.twitter.com/KAn0VUMSlZ</a></p><p> — KNEECAP (@KNEECAPCEOL) <a href="https://twitter.com/KNEECAPCEOL/status/1904306133814407522?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">March 24, 2025</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p> Many in the entertainment world shared the story online, and called for Ballal&#39;s release. <a href="https://x.com/KNEECAPCEOL/status/1904306133814407522">Kneecap reacted with a post on X</a> that read: “Beaten savagely by illegal Israel “settlers” and when the ambulance arrived to help him he was abducted by the IDF.”</p><p> The latter claim is disputed by the IDF&#39;s statement above.</p><p> They continued: “This is Palestine every single day. A total and brutal occupation on every level imaginable. FUCK US-BACKED ISRAEL.” The Irish rap trio have repeatedly spoken out against the conflict in Gaza, most recently <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/kneecap-hit-out-at-breaking-of-gaza-ceasefire-fuck-israel-3848123">hitting out at Israel after the breaking of the ceasefire</a> last week (March 21).</p><p> In their Cover feature for <i>NME</i> last year, <a href="https://www.nme.com/the-cover/kneecap-03-06-2024-3761722">KNEECAP also made a stance against what they called Israel&#39;s “occupation and genocide” of Gaza</a> . They also helped raise nearly £100,000 for a volunteer gym in the Aida Refugee Camp in Palestine, and loudly broadcast their message via social media and <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-kneecap-make-explosive-us-tv-debut-on-jimmy-fallon-3599087">high-profile TV appearances</a> .</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/oscars-refused-to-issue-statement-in-support-of-kidnapped-palestinian-filmmaker-co-director-claims-3849496">Oscars refused to issue statement in support of kidnapped Palestinian filmmaker, co-director claims</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
