t/uploads/2024/07/robert-downey-jr-jesse-grant-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/robert-downey-jr-jesse-grant-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/robert-downey-jr-jesse-grant-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/robert-downey-jr-jesse-grant-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/robert-downey-jr-jesse-grant-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/marvel-cinematic-universe">Marvel</a> is announcing the cast of <a href="https://www.nme.com/films/avengers-doomsday"><em>Avengers: Doomsday</em></a> in unusual fashion, and it&#39;s safe to say fans have been taken by surprise.</p><p> Each cast member is currently being announced in a livestream on Marvel Entertainment&#39;s <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Iy7k3aJS0Fw" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube</a> and official social media channels, with a new name being revealed every 12 minutes. You can find the updating cast list at the bottom of this article.</p><p> Among the returning cast members are Chris Hemsworth as Thor; Anthony Mackie as Sam Wilson, his <em>Captain America: Brave New World</em> his co-star Danny Ramirez as Joaquin Torres/The Falcon; Sebastian Stan as Bucky Barnes/the Winter Soldier; Paul Rudd as Scott Lang/Ant-Man; Tom Hiddleston as Loki; Letitia Wright as Shuri; and her <em>Black Panther: Wakanda Forever</em> co-star Winston Duke as M&#39;Baku.</p><p> Some recent newcomers to the MCU have also been announced for <em>Doomsday</em> . They include Vanessa Kirby as the Invisible Woman, Joseph Quinn as Human Torch and Ebon Moss-Bachrach as the Thing from this summer&#39;s <a href="https://www.nme.com/films/the-fantastic-four-first-steps"><em>The Fantastic Four: First Steps</em></a> . </p><figure id="attachment_3783119" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3783119" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3783119" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/robert-downey-jr-michael-buckner-1.jpg" alt="Robert Downey Jr" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/robert-downey-jr-michael-buckner-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/robert-downey-jr-michael-buckner-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/robert-downey-jr-michael-buckner-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/robert-downey-jr-michael-buckner-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/robert-downey-jr-michael-buckner-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/robert-downey-jr-michael-buckner-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3783119" class="wp-caption-text"> Robert Downey Jr will retune to the MCU in Avengers: Doomsday. Credit: Michael Bucker/Getty</figcaption></figure><p> A number of <a href="https://www.nme.com/films/thunderbolts"><em>Thunderbolts*</em></a> stars have also been confirmed, including Florence Pugh as Yelena Belova, David Harbour as Red Guardian, Wyatt Russell as US Agent, Hannah John-Kamen as Ghost, Lewis Pullman as the mysterious Bob, and Simu Liu as Shang-Chi.</p><p> Tenoch Huerta Mejía, who portrayed the underwater villain Namor in <em>Black Panther: Wakanda Forever</em> , has also been announced for <em>Doomsday,</em> as has Kelsey Grammer, who reprised his <em>X-Men</em> role as Beast in the post-credits scene of <em>The Marvels.</em></p><p> The cast list will continue to update for a further three hours, with the latest announcements being Sir Patrick Stewart, who looks set to reprise his role as Professor Charles Xavier, and Sir Ian McKellen, who will be returning as Magneto. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="复仇者：世界末日| Cast Announce" width="696" height="522" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Iy7k3aJS0Fw?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Suffice to say, Marvel fans have been left somewhat surprised and confused by the unconventional cast announcements, with many noting that the reveals are spoiling <em>Thunderbolts*</em> before its release, given we now know which characters will survive.</p><p> “Is there really any reason to watch <em>Thunderbolts</em> at this point?!?!” posted one fan on X, while another wrote: “Exciting but you&#39;re spoiling <em>Thunderbolts</em> !!”</p><p> Another jokingly remarked: “Girl, just post a list. This is taking forever.”</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> Is there really any reason to watch Thunderbolts at this point?!?!</p><p> — sts125 (@sts1251) <a href="https://twitter.com/sts1251/status/1904943907940581481?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">March 26, 2025</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> Exciting but you&#39;re spoiling Thunderbolts!!</p><p> — Francisco Munoz (@Xxak47boomxX) <a href="https://twitter.com/Xxak47boomxX/status/1904943248478515403?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">March 26, 2025</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p></p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> Girl just post a list. This is taking forever</p><p> — Demitric (@Demitric) <a href="https://twitter.com/Demitric/status/1904944923490861316?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">March 26, 2025</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p>